@Node "sunau.datatype()" "sunau.datatype/sunau.datatype"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
	sunau.datatype -- data type for Sun Audio sounds.

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
	The sunau data type, a sub-class of the @{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}, is used
	to load and save Sun Audio files.

@{b}    METHODS@{ub}
	OM_NEW -- Create a new sound object from an .AU file.   Creating an 
            empty object (DTST_RAM) is also supported and allows you to create
            .AU files.

        DTM_WRITE -- For DTWM_RAW an .AU file will be created. DTWM_IFF is 
            passed to the superclass.

@{b}    BUGS@{ub}
        Not very well tested! Encodings 1-5 are only not supported.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}.

@EndNode

